com.here.android.mpa.streetlevel

Class StreetLevelIconPlacement

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.here.android.mpa.streetlevel.StreetLevelIconPlacement

  • public final class StreetLevelIconPlacement
extends java.lang.Object
    Encapsulates the placement properties for all image-based street-level objects (StreetLevelIcon or StreetLevelBillboard) that users can add to a StreetLevelModel. Changes to properties of this interface are reflected in the display of the associated StreetLevelIcon or StreetLevelBillboard.

      • setVerticalPlacementHeight

        public StreetLevelIconPlacement setVerticalPlacementHeight(float height)
        Sets the vertical placement height value. The height parameter has a different meaning depending on the placement mode.
        Parameters:
        height -
        • If the horizontal placement mode is StreetLevelIconPlacement.HorizontalPlacement.TRACK_CAMERA, height is the vertical distance in meters from the camera.
        • If the vertical placement mode is StreetLevelIconPlacement.VerticalPlacement.TERRAIN, height is the distance in meters above the terrain.
        • If the vertical placement mode is StreetLevelIconPlacement.VerticalPlacement.FACADE and horizontal placement is StreetLevelIconPlacement.HorizontalPlacement.FACADE, height is the desired height in meters above the terrain. However, if this value is lower than the facade's default street-level object height, the default will be used instead. For all other horizontal placements modes, the interpretation is the same as for StreetLevelIconPlacement.VerticalPlacement.TERRAIN.
        • If the vertical placement mode is StreetLevelIconPlacement.VerticalPlacement.ATTACHMENT, height is a scale factor relative to the attached building height, where 0 is bottom of the building and 1 is top. Values can be outside of [0,1] range.
        • If the vertical placement mode is StreetLevelIconPlacement.VerticalPlacement.DEFAULT, height is the meters above sea level.
        Returns:
        This StreetLevelIconPlacement object
        See Also:
        StreetLevelIconPlacement.VerticalPlacement, StreetLevelIconPlacement.HorizontalPlacement
